<mixertitle>Overview of <mixer var="GAP3"/></mixertitle>

<h3>
  <mixer var="GAP3"/> provides:
</h3>
<ul>
  <li>
    A <a href="/Gap3/Manual3/C002S000.htm">programming&nbsp;language</a>,
    also called GAP, which is interpreted. Note that the
    language of <mixer var="GAP3"/> differs in some details from that of
    <mixer var="GAP4"/> (see <a href="/Gap3/Changes3/changes.html">
    <mixer var="GAP3"/>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<mixer var="GAP4"/></a>).
    The language features:
    <ul>
      <li>
        Pascal-like control structures,
      </li>
      <li>
        automatic memory management including garbage collection,
      </li>
      <li>
        built-in data types for key algebraic objects,
      </li>
      <li>
        flexible <a href="/Gap3/Manual3/C027S000.htm">list</a> and
        <a href="/Gap3/Manual3/C045S000.htm">record</a> data types.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    An interactive
    <a href="/Gap3/Manual3/C003S000.htm">environment</a> that supports
    debugging and timing of GAP programs, and provides
    online access to the reference manual as well as interactive help.
  </li>
  <li>
    A <a href="/Gap3/Manual3/chapters.htm">library</a> of
    <a href="/Gap3/Manual3/C002S018.htm">functions</a>
    containing implementations of various algebraic
    algorithms written in the GAP language. Besides using
    them you can also look at them to find how they work, and use them as
    examples for own programs. Although the <mixer var="GAP3"/> library
    provides over 4,000 functions, compare the manuals of
    <mixer var="GAP3"/> and <mixer var="GAP4"/> to see that the library
    of functions of <mixer var="GAP4"/> provides by far more functionality
    than that of <mixer var="GAP3"/>.
  </li>
  <li>
    Separate <a href="/Gap3/Packages3/packages.html">share&nbsp;packages</a>
    consisting of additional libraries of functions for specialized purposes.
  </li>
  <li>
    <a href="/Gap3/Datalib3/datalib.html">Data&nbsp;libraries</a> containing
    lists of large classes of algebraic objects that are accessible by using
    <mixer var="GAP3"/> commands.
  </li>
  <li>
    <a href="/Gap3/Doc3/doc.html">Documentation</a>, in particular
    <ul>
      <li>
        an introduction, called
        <a href="/Gap3/Manual3/C001S000.htm">About&nbsp;GAP</a>,
      </li>
      <li>
        the
        <a href="/Gap3/Doc3/manual.html">
        <mixer var="GAP3"/>&nbsp;Reference&nbsp;Manual</a>
        with complete descriptions of all library functions with examples
        of use,
      </li>
      <li>
        manuals for the <mixer var="GAP3"/>
        '<a href="/Gap3/Packages3/packages.html">share&nbsp;packages</a>'
        that are given as chapters 56 to 86 of the manual,
      </li>
      <li>
        worked out higher level
        <a href="/Gap3/Doc3/Examples3/examples.html">
        <mixer var="GAP3"/>&nbsp;examples</a>,
      </li>
      <li>
        an <a href="/Doc/forumarchive.html">archive</a> of GAP
        Forum contributions,
      </li>
      <li>
        a <a href="/Doc/Bib/bib.html">bibliography</a> of papers quoting
        GAP,
      </li>
      <li>
        and a <a href="/Doc/Talks/talks.html">collection</a> of preprints
        and talks related to GAP.
      </li>
    </ul>
    Note that the last three points refer to information for both,
    <mixer var="GAP3"/> and <mixer var="GAP4"/>.
  </li>
  <li>
    <a href="/Gap3/Download3/download.html">Download</a> and Installation
    instructions.
  </li>
  <li>
    <a href="/Faq/faq.html">FAQ</a> answers, some of which refer to
    <mixer var="GAP4"/>.
  </li>
</ul>

<h3>
  Structure of <mixer var="GAP3"/>
</h3>
<p>
  <mixer var="GAP3"/> has a kernel written in C. It implements
</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      the <mixer var="GAP3"/> language,
    </li>
    <li>
      an interactive environment for developing and using <mixer var="GAP3"/>
      programs,
    </li>
    <li>
      memory management, and
    </li>
    <li>
      fast versions of time critical operations for various data types. 
    </li>
  </ul>
<p>
  All the rest of the library of functions is written in the
  <mixer var="GAP3"/> language.
</p>

<h3>
  Requirements and Availability
</h3>
<p>
  <mixer var="GAP3"/> will run on any machine with a UNIX-like or recent
  Windows or MacOS operating system. For hardware requirements see the
  <mixer var="GAP3"/> <a href="/Gap3/Download3/download.html">download</a>
  instructions.
</p>

</mixer>
